Comment 1: 
func(float64) (float64 float64) is a valid type. It returns a float64, and it documents
that the name of that return value is float64. 

For example:
package main

func pr(float64 float64) {
    println(float64)
}

func main() {
    pr(3.14)
}

http://play.golang.org/p/sc-iX3PnGf
